# 🚂 NS 1069 – Virginian

Welcome to the Virginian Heritage Exhibit.

Norfolk Southern Heritage Unit **NS 1069** honors the legacy of the Virginian Railway, a railroad known for its efficient coal operations and commitment to innovation. This exhibit preserves my personal history with NS 1069, documenting every catch, photograph, video, and memory as part of the TrainsForever Archive Museum.

---

## 📖 Railroad History

The **Virginian Railway** was founded in **1907** to transport high-quality coal from the coalfields of West Virginia to the port of Norfolk, Virginia. Despite being a relatively small railroad, it earned a reputation for modern equipment, efficient operations, and well-maintained infrastructure.

In **1959**, the Virginian Railway merged with the Norfolk & Western Railway. Today, **Norfolk Southern Heritage Unit NS 1069** honors that legacy by wearing a modern interpretation of the railroad's classic black and yellow paint scheme.

